<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Ok son.... this comes straight from the mouth of the gods, of from a 31st level wizard, which should be close enough for you.<p>

 At level 9, things are hard. I recommend not fighting so much for loot at this point as for exp. The closer you get to 12 the easiest the money will come in, as by that point you'll want to move up to dervishes, and with any luck and a decent group, you should come out of about a hour of derv fighting with a few pp.<br>
   If you can't get a derv group, solo hunt bears for HQ Bear Skins, skeletons for bone chips, spiders for silks, zombies for skins.... the list goes on and on. The easiest way to make money is to find something someone else wants and sell it to them. Simple fact of life. Since you're in... probably around CB, you could jaunt over to FP and fight there awhile, but if you want to stay near Felwithe, you're just gonna have to put up with the CB belts. OR... if you're really strapped for cash, sell your belts 1pp apiece. There's always someone who wants them.<br>
    After you hit about 10 or 11 you really should think about sailing over to Freeport and finding a Dev group in either West Commonlands or North Ro. The mone will come in pretty hot and heavy that way and the exp is good.<br>
  All right man, hope this hepled, and you take care of yourself. Thee's not enough wizards around as it is these days. ::Grins::<p>

  ~Pratz Strike.<hr>When I make you laugh I have completed a little bit more of my life's work.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
